item.title: Victoria Silvstedt
item.dc:creator: @eVokki1 Cowie`
item.description:
@eVokki1 wrote:

I use the photofilters at around 30% strength and then I lowered the fill and opacicity, The bit of her face that you see, I used the marquee tool to get a section, then I duplicated it, making two copies, angled them to a V-Shape and erased the majority with spatter settings.

item.title: Victoria Silvstedt
item.dc:creator: @exe626 exe626
item.description:
@exe626 wrote:

You used a photofilter at 100% strength? If you did that you should have at least lowered opacity on it a bit. Also, you say you only used one clipping mask? Then whats that small image of her face doing there? I just figured it was a clipping mask, I didn’t expect you to go to such lengths to erase everything around that particular spot and use it.

item.title: Victoria Silvstedt
item.dc:creator: @eVokki1 Cowie`
item.description:
@eVokki1 wrote:

[quote=“exe626, post:8, topic:156230”]You shouldn’t have made her only one color, that kills its. Then that clipping mask is just ew. Seriously, who told these people to randomly slap a clipping mask in there? I understand sometimes, its pretty good looking. But now, wtf? The effects are fine, they balance it out, but the colors are horrendous. Text could use some(a lot) of work.

4/10[/quote]

The only cliping mask used was on the text, the colours, they are a direct consiquence for using a photo filter. I see where your coming from, but the signature is meant to be mono toned.
